snippet.textDisplay:
The best part of Jenna's dog videos is watching her love on her dogs. It makes me so happy to see how loved her dogs are, and how much she pays attention to their needs. For example, Italian Greyhounds are a lot like my Beagle - they are smart enough to know that they don't have to listen to you (and can be super hyper) - they aren't really "lap dogs". But, you can see Kermit and Peaches in so many videos just sitting there (the dog train video or this video or the one where she makes her dogs treats) because they trust Jenna and know that she's looking out for them. Or Bunny's videos, where you can see Jenna and Julian treat her just amazingly and talk so well about how they are making her feel at home and meeting her where she's at, instead of trying to force her to behave in a particular way.

I wouldn't even say that Jenna's dogs are "well-trained" - I would say that she's created an environment where she works very, very hard to communicate with her dogs and listen to them, so they trust her. And, of course, my all-time favorite moment is still in the vlog where Kermit's tail is broken and THE SECOND that Jenna notices how weird it looks she says, "We have to go to the vet rn" - despite the fact that they just got back from the airport and suspect it's a bug bite - and Julian instantly goes, "Okay!".


Jenna + Julian + the dogs are my OTP <3 I watch her dog videos whenever I'm feeling down and they make me so happy.
